Direct participation in the activities of the project organisation and main organisation at the practical training site. Analysis of the development of the project portfolio of the organisation. Analysis and evaluation of a completed/ongoing/planned project, incl. the project environment, personnel, risks, financing. Analysis of the cooperation partners, public relations and team work of the project. Critical analysis of one's own work performance and effectiveness of the practical project training. Preparation of the report on practical training.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Project placement aims at reinforcing and deepening the student's theoretical knowledge of project design and management by providing the student with the opportunity to gain experience in using project management methods and tools in a practical work environment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing  project management practice, the student is able to: * describe and analyse projects; * evaluate and, if necessary, recommend various project management methods; * analyse aspects of financial activities and personnel in projects; * analyse the influence of project management on an organisation in cooperation with specialists.
